 \frac{n!}{(n-x+1)!}\cdot (x-1); 
 P[X=x]=\frac{n!(x-1)}{(n-x+1)!n^x}=\frac{x-1}{n}\prod_{i=0}^{x-2}\left(1-\frac{i}{n}\right). 
 E[X]=\sum_{x}xP[X=x]=\sum_{x=2}^{n+1}\frac{x(x-1)}{n}\prod_{i=0}^{x-2}\left(1-\frac{i}{n}\right). 
